The spell is cast over a weapon of the Adept's choice causing it to
burst into flame but without causing damage to the weapon or its
wielder. The Strike Chance to hit a target with the weapon is
increased by 1 (+ 1 / Rank), and damage is increased by 1 / 2 Ranks of
the Adept. When the weapon is used against a creature of cold or water
or against the Undead, damage increases to 1 / Rank. All creatures
that live in cold environments or in water are considered creatures of
cold or water. At rank 11 any hand-held weapon may be created from
fire. Such weapons have little actual weight, but strength and
dexterity requirements must be met as per normal. Missiles may also be
affected by this spell, but not missile weapons, thus an arrow may be
enflamed but not a bow.
