\begin{spell}[G-8]{Protection Against Magical Fire}
d334 2
a335 1
\range{Touch}
d337 20
a356 2
\multiple{175}
\basechance{15\%}
d358 2
a359 2
\storage{1. Potion; 2. Investment}
\target{Entity}
d361 12
a372 14
The target is protected against all magical forms of fire, or against
fire spells according to the rank of the spell.  If cast on the Adept,
the effective rank of the damaging fire is reduced by the Rank of this
spell, to a minimum of no effect.  If cast on another target, the
effective rank of the damaging fire spell is reduced by half the Rank
of this spell, to a minimum of Rank 0.  If a damaging effect is not
caused by a spell or ritual its effective Rank is held to be equal to
the ``plus'' to the damage die.

\begin{example}
If a dragon's breath does [D + 25] damage, then it is said to have an
effective Rank of 25, so a Rank 12 Protection from Magical Fire will
reduce the damage to [D + 13].
\end{example}
a376 1

d378 8
a385 9

\duration{Concentration: maximum 1 hour + 1 / Rank}
\multiple{750}
\basechance{9\% + 5\ / Rank}
\resist{May not be resisted (passively by creatures of fire)}
\target{Any fire}
\casttime{1 hour}
\material{A fire}
\actions{Concentration}
d388 21
a408 8
The Adept can bind the element of fire to their will by performing a
Ritual of Binding fire in an area where fire already exists.  The
ritual requires that the Adept spend one hour of time. If the Ritual
Check is less than or equal to 9\% (+ 5 / Rank), the ritual is
successful and the fire source over which the ritual was cast is
considered bound for a length of time equal to the ability of the
adept to retain concentration over it (maximum of 1 hour + 1
additional hour per Rank).
d410 3
a412 18
The chance that the ritual will be successful is modified by the
following numbers:

\begin{tabularx}{\linewidth}{X@@{\hspace{0.5em}}r}
For every 5 feet separating the Adept from the fire being bound & -4\% \\
\end{tabularx}

A bound fire can be shaped by the Adept who bound it into any desired
form.  Its size may be increased to a size which is greater than its
original size by a factor equal to the square of the Adept's rank.
The Adept can instill in the fire intelligence equal to the their own.
The higher the Adept's Rank with the ritual, the greater the results
of the ritual.  Whereas at Rank 1, the Adept could create a Fire
Creature which would have to be guided at every turn, at Rank 10, the
same Fire Creature might be endowed with free will, but would be loyal
to the purposes of the Adept.  The ritual cannot be resisted except by
an intelligent being composed of fire (and then only passive
resistance is possible).
d418 8
a425 9
\begin{spell}[S-1]{Wall of Fire}

\range{ 10 feet + 10 / Rank}
\duration{10 minutes + 10 / Rank}
\multiple{100}
\basechance{25\%}
\resist{May only be passively resisted}
\storage{Investment, Ward, Magical Trap}
\target{Area}
d427 13
a439 29
The Adept can create a 5 foot high \x 20 foot long \x 1 foot
thick wall of flames, or a 5 foot high \x 1 foot thick circle of
flames with a 5 foot radius, or a pillar 15 feet high with a 2 foot
radius.  The Adept can increase any one dimension by 1 foot per Rank.
The wall cannot be seen through, and cannot be cast so as to be in
contact with any entity.  Any entity coming into contact with the wall
must resist or suffer [D - 5] (+ 1 / Rank) Fire damage.  The wall
will provide light equivalent to a Firelight spell large campfire.

The entirety of one edge must be affixed to a surface.  This means
that a wall can be created with a smaller dimension than would
otherwise be possible.  For example, casting a wall of fire on a
stepping stone that is 3' square will result in a wall which is only
3' long.  Any edge may be affixed but, for the purposes of this spell,
this does not include either face.  (For example, a wall could not be
placed flat on a large open surface). The surface or surfaces that the
Wall of fire is affixed to do not need to be flat, but the length of
the wall is measured from the deepest depression on the surface that
the wall fills.  (For example, a circularly concave wall of 5' radius,
with a rank 0 wall affixed to it will end in a flit edge 15' beyond
the end of the curvature).  The entire anchoring edge must be visible
to the Adept.  The wall itself cannot be moved.  Should an entire
cross-section of the last remaining anchoring edge be removed then the
wall will immediately dissipate.  (For example, an adept casts a wall
1' off the ground, attached to a door.  As soon as the door is opened
the wall is dissipated.  If, however, the adept had cast it so that it
overlapped the door frame, and it projected slightly above the top of
the door, then it would not have been dissipated because no entire
cross-section of the anchoring edge has been removed.
