\begin{ritual}[R-1]{Summoning and Controlling Fire Elemental}

\duration{Concentration: No maximum}
\multiple{250}
\basechance{MA + 5\% / Rank + 1\% / WP over 15}
d747 4
a750 5
\target{Fire Elemental}
\casttime{2 hours}
\material{None}
\actions{Concentration}
\concentration{Standard}
d752 6
a757 15
The Adept may summon a Fire Elemental and bind it to temporary service
by performing this ritual.  If the Ritual Check is less than or equal
to the summoner's Base Chance, then the Elemental is summoned and
controlled.  If the ritual backfires and the Elemental appears, but is
uncontrolled and will attack the summoner and their friends.  Any
other result has no effect.

A Fire Elemental always appears within 20 feet of the summoner.  It
has a combined Endurance and Fatigue equal to (15 + 15 / Rank) and,
unless controlled by the summoner will attack and burn until dispelled
by a Special Knowledge Counterspell of the College of Fire Magics.
Once controlled, the Fire Elemental remains controlled until the
summoner's concentration is broken or they choose to send the
Elemental back to its own dimension with a Special Knowledge
Counterspell of this College or it is banished.
